  "prompt": "What is the sum of all the integers less than 100 which leave a remainder 2 when divided by 5?",
  "response": "To find the sum of all integers less than 100 that leave a remainder of 2 when divided by 5, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Identify the Sequence:**\n   \n   Such numbers can be expressed in the form:\n   \\[\n   n = 5k + 2 \\quad \\text{where} \\quad k \\text{ is an integer and } n < 100\n   \\]\n   \n2. **Determine the Range for \\( k \\):**\n   \n   Solve for \\( k \\) in \\( 5k + 2 < 100 \\):\n   \\[\n   5k + 2 < 100 \\\\\n   5k < 98 \\\\\n   k < \\frac{98}{5} \\\\\n   k < 19.6\n   \\]\n   \n   Since \\( k \\) must be an integer, the maximum value for \\( k \\) is 19.\n   \n   Therefore, the sequence of numbers is:\n   \\[\n   2, 7, 12, 17, \\ldots, 97\n   \\]\n   \n3. **Verify the Last Term:**\n   \n   Substitute \\( k = 19 \\) into the formula:\n   \\[\n   n = 5 \\times 19 + 2 = 95 + 2 = 97 \\quad (\\text{which is less than 100})\n   \\]\n   \n4. **Determine the Number of Terms:**\n   \n   This is an arithmetic sequence with the first term \\( a_1 = 2 \\) and common difference \\( d = 5 \\).\n   \n   The number of terms \\( N \\) is:\n   \\[\n   N = 19 + 1 = 20 \\quad \\text{(since \\( k \\) ranges from 0 to 19)}\n   \\]\n   \n5. **Calculate the Sum of the Sequence:**\n   \n   The sum \\( S \\) of an arithmetic sequence is given by:\n   \\[\n   S = \\frac{N}{2} \\times (a_1 + a_N)\n   \\]\n   where \\( a_N \\) is the last term.\n   \n   Substituting the known values:\n   \\[\n   S = \\frac{20}{2} \\times (2 + 97) \\\\\n   S = 10 \\times 99 \\\\\n   S = 990\n   \\]\n   \n**Final Answer:**\n\\[\n\\boxed{990}\n\\]",
